 grade, some sort of cultured marble vanity top and old fixtures. The towels were thin and coarse.Overall, we knew about the poor location relative to the Strip, had low expectations and paid a little more to at least be able to sleep in a decent room. I would have to say that if you know what you are getting into, if you get a cheap rate, it's not too bad. Its location enabled us to quickly get on our way to Zion and Bryce.	
