Oct 28 2009 	A nice first time trip to Las Vegas for my friends	I took a group of co-workers to Las Vegas for their first time and we stayed at the Stratosphere. On booking, we were looking for price deals and I knew this property was offering the nicest rooms at a $30.00 a night rate. Circus Circus and Hooters had similar deals, but the rooms were in their motor courts.We were pleasantly surprized! The rooms were basic but clean and well cared for. The hotel had many ammenities and we felt a sense of safety as a group of women traveling without male companionship. Staff were friendly and helpful. My friends are not seasoned gamblers, but the casino workers took the time to explain the games to them in a kind, friendly and courteous manner. The slots payed off well and they have a large selection of the latest multi-wager penny machines. We had several meals in Lucky's and Roxies and enjoyed the quality and quantities of the portions we were served.The resort's only downfall is its' location. You must take a bus or taxi to any other attraction you want to visit. A $12.00 cab fare for four will get you to go to either the strip hotels or Fremont Street. It was a small price to pay for the value received.I will be taking another group of nurses to Las Vegas in February, and plan to stay at the Stratosphere again. I normally book the Mandalay Bay, but this property is the best bang for our bucks!	
