es of having to stand outside of the room, with all of our bags and luggage waiting for a room key.We then proceeded down to our new room, which was conveniently only two doors down. Unfortunately, the floor in this room was again soaking wet, and the room smelled very strongly of cleaning products. At this, we headed downstairs to the front desk, to speak with the manager. We arrived at the desk/check-in area where the manager was, and had been acknowledged by her. She informed us that she was logging on to her terminal, and would help us shortly. We stood there, at the front desk for around 5-10 minutes before we were addressed again by the manager. She was sitting directly in front of us, doing nothing this entire time. At this point, we were fed up, and asked to be refunded for our room and that we would be staying at a different hotel, at this time the manager snapped back at us, asking us why we wanted to receive a refund. At no point prior to this were we asked why we had come to see her. We then stated what had happened with our first room, how long we spent having to wait for a key, and how our second room had the exact same problem. After a bit of discussion, we were checked out of the room, and a refund was issued. We finally got out of the hotel around 4:00pm. We then had to take a monorail back to the southern end of the strip, ($15 for the three of us) and check back in to our first hotel, which cost us $140 more for the night than we were expecting to pay if we had stayed at the Stratosphere. As well, we lost out on our opportunity to go up in the tower for free, which would be included with our room due to checking out from this room and service problem, and decided against paying $15 each to the hotel where we were treated so poorly. After checking back in to the New York New York at around 5:30pm, we headed up to our room to rest after our long journey of checking into the Stratosphere. Needless to say, our last day of our trip was ruined, and we boarded our plane the next morning at 9:45am to head home.	
