Sep 24 2009 	Way better than I expected!	Can't praise the Stratosphere enough! From the check in service to the room cleanliness I could find no fault with this hotel. We paid about 27 per night for 5 nights in September and on arrival they didn't have two non-smoking king rooms together, so they gave us a free upgrade! The pool area was spotless, the guest relations desk were great. I'd recommend making as much use of the concierge as possible. We had questions for them every day and they were incredibly helpful and even booked a tour for us. The buffet is excellent value for money but one tip - get a rewards card as soon as you get there. You get a 25% discount in the buffet restaurant and it's definitley worth it. We ate there every morning and on three days we ate there in the evening too. For $19.99 you can eat there unlimited all day. Stratosphere offers a brunch buffet so don't be surprised to find spaghetti bolognese on offer for breakfast! Service in the restaurant is excellent and I recommend a visit to Roxy's Diner, on the casino floor. Great food (again, better value if you have your rewards card) and the servers even sing classic hits for you!! I'd definitely stay there again.	
