Aug 8 2009 	Wonderful Time at the Stratosphere	After reading some of the previous reviews, I was a bit worried about staying at the Stratosphere and went in with very low expectations. However I must say I really enjoyed my stay at the Stratosphere. Upon arrival we were told that there were no more non smoking rooms with a king size bed which we had booked. This was quickly resolved we were given a free upgrade to the 23rd floor which had a wonderful view. The rooms are a bit dated which I knew going in. However housekeeping did a wonderful job and the rooms were very clean. The food at the various restaurants were good but I really enjoyed the $20 all day buffet. The food selections were very good. The trip to the tower (which is included in the price) was very good and gave a breathtaking view of las vegas. The only thing which I did not like was the hotel was a little far from the main action on the strip, however the $7 all day deuce bus pass was well worth the price. However based on value for money I would difenately stay here again.	
