Aug 7 2009 	Worth Staying here just for the trip up the tower	The view from atop the Strat is magnificent, and if you plan to see it, consider a stay here. At $16 per person to go to the top, that's $32 for a couple, and our room, with taxes, cost us $37 (yes, Vegas is begging people to come right now). Unlimited trips to the top are included with your hotel stay. (As regards the 4 star rating, I view ratings as within a price category, that is, value for the money. Actually, at the bargain price offered, I should probably give the Strat a 5, but somehow that seems excessive. It is, simply, a nice enough place that is currently a terrific bargain.)The accommodations are nice: A clean, refurbished room, attractively decorated, comfortable Serta mattress, large, comfortable bath tub. The hotel pool is plenty nice enough, though not special or memorable. Not sure I'd stay here for more than two nights (because of its location), but it's a bargain right now if you plan to go up the tower. And if you are braver than I am, you have your choice of 3 rides up there. Enjoy!	
