Aug 5 2009 	Our stay was perfect!!!	I must admit I was a little worried about staying here because of the location but my mind was put to rest when we pulled into the parking garage and security was patrolling the area on bikes (and keep in mind there were about 5-6 of them and at 3am). We checked in rather late at 3 in the morning and waited in line about 15 minutes. The girl at check in was so nice. She was very apologetic about our wait (which compared to The Flamingo we checked out of was nothing). She gave us a coupon book to use around the casino. It is a great coupon book and we used a lot of the coupons in it including a coupon for free admission to the top of the tower (which was amazing by the way). We ate at several restaurants including the diner, which was fun and Top of the World (a must try). We stayed in a suite one night and a standard room another night. Both rooms were clean, in good condition, and quiet. There was always someone cleaning and people actually smile and greet you here as opposed to some other hotels we have stayed at in Las Vegas. The beds are comfortable and the linens are a clean, crisp white. The showers are hot and have good water pressure. The other thing we enjoyed about this hotel was that it has a very convenient lay out. There are many things for families to do here including a large swimming pool, small arcade and amusement park rides at the top of the tower. I highly recommend The Stratosphere. We will be back.	
