Jul 14 2009 	Excellent Gaming!!!	I stayed at the Stratosphere for a 3 night stay this July. I initially booked a Premier Tower room, but once I checked in, I asked about an ugrade to a Suite. I ended up getting an Executive Suite for a total of $200 more for all 3 nights. Altogether, the move was worth it as the Suite offered better strip views and such comfortable space to relax in the room. The only drawback was that it came with a King size bed (ok for couples) and a pull-out sofa bed. Between my buddy and I, that worked and we each had our own bed. Our room was in the Premier Tower on the 24th floor (top floor), located nearby the Private Pool on the 25th floor. he housekeeping was superb (Irene) and she made sure our place was always clean and new bed sheets.The gaming was excellent. The tables were always at $5 (most, if not all) and the Pit Bosses were so friendly, always encouraging to drinks and joining the Ultimate Rewards program that the hotel offers. What I specifically enjoyed were the people visiting and gambling there. There were many folks that are avid Startosphere gamblers/visitors. They seem to like staying there and gambling there. After my strip, I did too. I plan on returning later this year...	
Jul 14 2009 	Hotel is Fine Location is terrible	When I booked this hotel it was through a flight/hotel package on Expedia and I was looking for price over location. That turned out to be a bad idea. The hotel is perfectly serviceable. There was nothing wrong with the room and I enjoyed the casino. It is just so far down the strip that you have to take cabs everywhere. It is nowhere near any public transportation, at least not close enough so that I'd want to walk. I'd recommend staying at either Flamingo or TI, both centrally located and reasonably priced. Cabs there are also so expensive you're just better off paying $50-$100 more total for the hotel b/c you'll spend at least that in cabs.	
Jul 11 2009 	Great Family Value	We spent 4 days here with my two teen age children just prior to our wedding at the Bellagio. For the last 2 days we were joined by the &quot;Mom's&quot; (my mom and my soon to be mother in law). It was a great place for our needs-the kids loved the tower and the thrill rides, the McDonalds and the pizza place on the shopping level were big hits and even the mom's enjoyed the view from the indoor observation deck. We had a rental car and parking was easy. I definately recommend the Premier Tower rooms-access to the garage is quick, Starbucks is right at the elevators, and also access to the shopping level is easy. The best part was you don't have to walk across the casino every time you come and go. We have stayed in both towers and the Premier is definately better. Our room was clean and the staff was good at keeping it that way, despite 2 messy teenagers and their exploding suitcases. The pool area was great, although the really loud holiday weekend dj was a little bit much. We were always able to get lounge chairs and it was never too crowded. Again, getting there from the Premier tower is super quick-just an elevator ride to the 8th floor. Our room was nicely decorated with 2 queen beds and a decent sized bathroom-roomy enough for the 4 of us to all be there at the same time and not fall over each other. (again, much larger than the World Tower rooms). The rooms have been remodeled and look it. We had a view of the jumbo tron on the front of the building, the thrill rides above and a bit of the pool area. We ate at Roxys and Luckys and also frequented the Starbicks in the casino, where service is super fast. The kids really enjoyed Freemont Street. We also visited Red Rock Canyon, which I highly recommend. We want to go back in either the fall or early spring when the weather is more conducive to hiking. There's a new visitor center opening at Red Rock in the fall of 2009. We also ate at the nearby Tiffany's Diner, which was great, cheap and easy to get to. The White Cross Drugstore (Where the diner is located) sells very reasonable supplies-tooth paste, post cards, shampoo, even alcohol. We bought a styrofoam cooler for $2 to keep bottled water and drinks in our room. It worked out really well. Overall, the Stratosphere is a great value for families. We will go back with the kids again.	
