am one night and used the duece bus the rest of the three days. The bus gets a little old, but it can be very intertaining if you ride it with the right attitude. You meet some very interesting people on the bus.They have a McDonalds, Ben &amp; Jerrys and a pizza place on the second floor, which was nice if you wanted something quick and cheaper. We spluged one night and ate at the Top of the World. It's expensive, but the food was good and the service was excellent. The view was awesome at night.I guess if you are someone stuffy and picky spend your money on a more expensive hotel. I would rather use the money for a show or a really nice meal.	
