Mar 21 2009 	Best place to stay in Vegas if you are on a Budget!!!!!!!!!	This is the best place to stay if you are in Vegas on a budget and do not want to sacrifice location or the &quot;Vegas Experience&quot;The Hotel has gone under renovations and the rooms are definately in the 3 and a half star category. I find that 3 stars in Vegas is more like a 4 star hotel in Canada. Las Vegas hotels seem to be held to a tuffer standard. For example....... a Marriott hotel Alberta might be 4 stars, but a 4 star hotel in Las Vegas is twice as nice........ how does that work?Stratosphere is located at the very north end of the new Las Vegas strip. A short walk across the street to the Sahara hotel where the Monorail starts, and you can take the train to dozens of other resorts on the strip.Stratoshere seems like the best deal if youre on a budget, the shopping, restraunts, nightclub and hotel room rates are some of the best on the strip. Even the &quot;Top of the World&quot; restraunt is good value for what you get, as it is high quality food in an incredable setting high above Las Vegas in the tower, for a price that is better then comparable Las Vegas restraunts of this type. Another restraunt I woudl recomend is the 50's Diner on the main level. The food is wonderful, prices are very competative, and the 50's theme is amazing! The swimming pool is my fav because its got so much space for tanning and so many chairs that you never feel like its too full, theres always a place to lay back on a chair, and a spot in the pool, unlike comparable top las vegas pools. There is even an Adult pool seperate from the main pool area, the adult pool encourages women to go topless. I was there around noon and all I saw were out of shape old women going topless, but it was still fun!Ive been to the Stratosphere 3 times for several days at a time, and i have always found the staff really nice there. Since the hotel changed owners about a year ago, and the new management came in, I have found that the staff are even nicer, some of the most friendly front desk service ive experienced in Las Vegas. The Casino is great, lots of fun games, and a lot of the newer games that are popular, The resort has style and there is a mix of people about 60% chic-style tourists dressed to impress and 40% tourists that dress like slobs.-The only bad things i can say about the stratosphere are that the Hair Salon is a huge rip off, about 5 times as much money to get your hair trimed and styled as comparable salons off the strip and about 3 times as much as the salon across the street at the Sahara Resort. Also, due to the design of the hotel, some rooms have a view of air exchange and conditioning equiptment or views of cement walls 30 feet away.	
Mar 20 2009 	Yes and No!!	I stayed here for 10 nights with my partner and therer were some things I was happy with and some things I wasn't. We arrived about 7pm and were checked in within 10minutes, great after I had read about people waiting about an hour.I had paid for a premium view with a king bed. We were told that there were none available and werde given a premium view with two queen beds.The view was of a bad downtown area with nice mountains in the background, I guess its the mountains you pay for. The room was clean not very big but enough for a couple who only wanted it as a base. The housekeeping service was also good. The hotel amenities were decent, nothing special but nothing terrible, apart from the main pool being closed for refurb and the nightclub being permanently closed. The are three bars on the casino level, service in all three was dreadful but I noticed that generally in bars in Vegas there was nothing rushing the bartenders. The location of the hoel is right at the end of the strip, which is 4miles long, and although a 30 minute walk will get you to the main body of the strip, itsd not a nice walk and there is a cheap bus service right outside the hotel. The area around the hotel is a bit rough because its at the cheaper end of the strip, down where the motels begin and the beggers become a bit more aggresive, this is why the bus comes in handy!! The price compared to the main body of strip may cause you accept this, it did for me, but when a tour driver told me that the housing estate beside the hotel has a number of stabbings/shootings a week i though differently, but I didn't see anything like that. In total if you just want a decent hotel as a base then this hotel is fine. I would recommend it too a freind but not a fussy one!!	
