Mar 8 2009 	Good value for the price...	Just got back from a 3 night stay at the Stratosphere - Mar 2 - 5, 09.$31 + tax + resort fee for a 'premium' view room. Ended up in room # 31947 on the 19th floor. View was south toward the strip - the tower and the large Stratosphere front hotel sign obscure the view but you still see a large part of the city which is great.The room was clean, bed ( very good ) &amp; bedding is quite new, tv picture was a bit fuzzy and had limited channels. All in all the room was great especially for the price. Ate at the 50's style diner once which was good and they put everyone through quickly. The 2nd floor where the shops are located has a McDonalds etc which was nice and a cheaper alternative. The hotel gives you a coupon book for properties within the Stratosphere which is nice - mostly 10% off coupons which can add up.Casino is acceptable although can be a bit 'smoky' and has an older smell to it.Check in / out was simple. Parking is excellent if you have a car. I rented from Advantage which I had never heard of. Great rates. Booked right at the airport. $170 US plus gas for 4 full days. Dodge Nitro SUV which was perfect. Shuttle bus takes you from the airport to the car rental place which is about a 10 minute trip. Very efficient.This was my first time to Vegas. Renting a car is great. Easy to drive around Vegas and every casino except Freemont Street has free 'self parking' that has great access.Yes, this hotel is near the North end of the strip. If you plan on walking be in good shape... Again, the rental car option is well worth it.So, the hotel is not new by any means but the price is great, the 'premium rooms' are more than acceptable, the location is not great but rent a car or use the Deuce. You will be happy especially if you will only be in your room to sleep / shower.	
