Feb 10 2009 	Great Rates for hotel/ Bad Car rental agency	We found great rates for this hotel on Expedia. It is at the far end of the strip so it is a long walk. You can also take the double decker buses up and down the strip. The rooms were clean and the breakfast in the hotel was very reasonable.The line up was quite long to check in but that's what you get for $55 CAD/night.We rented a car from Dollar at the airport. They had great rates $9/day but the lineup was ridiculous - at least 1 1/2 - 2 hrs. I decided to take a taxi to the hotel and go back later but it was still over 1 hr. Only 3 people working each time. I will never rent with Dollar again. All the other agencies had no line up at all and there are at least 8 of them in the building.	
Feb 10 2009 	Great Deal	We stayed here for a weekend in January. My fiance, now husband, and I decided to 'runaway' to Las Vegas to get married, and this is where we chose to stay, while we got married at A Little White Chapel. We got a great deal. It was our first time out to Vegas. While it stunk to be a little far away from the strip, the Deuce for $7 you can ride all day long, and the stop is close to the hotel. The rooms were very clean and spacious. We had a great view of the strip from our room. Unfortunatley on the second night we were there (the night after we got married thankfully) I slipped and fell (apparently I'm a klutz) and hit my head pretty hard. The security staff came up, and then called the ambulance for me and unfortunately went to the ER. While of course it sucked having to go through that, the staff was very attentive and did a good job. The only complaint, our room door wasn't closed when we got back. But thankfully nothing got stolen.Besides the trip to the ER, it was a great trip.We also got buy 1, get 1 tickets for the American Superstars Show at the hotel. It was a great show, and definitely worth seeing.	
Feb 9 2009 	Great deal	I stayed here from Friday night to Sunday night, while staying here during the Consumer Electronics Show. I got an average rate of $78/night, which included their resort fee of $7.50 a day, which makes that low rate they advertise initially, not so low in the end.The Good:- I got a very large double room at the lowest room rate.- Room comes with working TV. - Room was thoroughly cleaned every day.- Friendly desk staff- Free admission to Stratosphere Tower.- Free parking- Great view of I-15 from one of the towers.- Very comfortable; no noise issue.- While neighborhood gets a bad rap from other reviewers, not much of an issue if you have a rental car.- With rental car, location from rest of Strip is not an issue.- They let you check out through your cell phone. I was not going to get out of the room by check-out time of 11 a.m., so I called and they gave me a few minutes. You have to go to desk to get printout of final receipt though.The Bad:- Resort fee of $7.50 a day.- Long walk from room and elevator to parking lot.- Not most centralized location if you have no rental car.- Early check-out time of 11 a.m.	
Feb 7 2009 	Were married here and stayed here...returning this March	I stayed here 3/2006 and we were married in one of the chapels. The hotel was very clean for the price...back then it was around 45 something a room...this year with the slowing economy we are staying for 27 a night. You just can't beat it. We thought of staying somewhere else, but for the price and we know it's CLEAN which is most important we decided to stay again. We use the Deuce for transportation so it's location from central strip isn't a big deal to us. Everyone who helped us with the wedding was great...the photo's were great, but expensive.We seen American Superstars while here with discount tickets...it was fun. Top of the world has a wonderful view and atmosphere, food was just minimal :( We ate at Lucky's Cafe I think it was called...it was good and fair priced!I'm staying again March 8-12, 2009!	
