Feb 1 2009 	Value	Ok yeah its out of the way.. Not good for first timers or second timers.. However, get a players card.. they send me free offers everymonth for the last 3 years.. The offers are good ones. 3 or 4 free nights and a whole lot of freeplay.. slot tourneys.. food credit ect ect.. Cant beat it if your into the freebies.. Honestly ill stay here a few nights then move to another hotel for a few days when i want the frills.. The deals here are worth it. New beds in 08 and the rooms are more then enough to get a good nights or good days rest.. The pools are cool and fun.. good drinks and parties in the pool area . I have no problm staying here but i have been to Vegas 15 or 20 times and have seen it all.. Good place if your on a budget and you have a rental car.. Dont stay here if this is your first few times in Vegas..	
Jan 31 2009	Love it!	I have stayed here twice now and love it. It's clean, the beds are large and very comfy, bathroom was clean and well equipped with towels, food from room service was good and always served within half an hour of ordering. All the staff we dealt with were helpful and friendly (on both occasions) and the views are okay - but to be honest, who wants to sit in their room staring out of the window all the time?! There is FAR too much to do and see in Vegas. I used the deuce bus on my most recent trip but unfortunately, all the drivers were extremely rude - they are obviously sick to the back teeth of tourists, especially from overseas, and it shows. The fares have risen slightly now - $3 one way and $7 for a 24 hour pass. Still excellent value for money - if you are brave enough. There's also the monorail which runs to/from various hotels on the Strip - again, good value for money at $5 a single trip and $13 for 24 hours but you have to negotiate the hotel lobbies and casinos and end up walking miles just to get to the stations. The nearest stop to the Stratosphere is at the nearby Sahara hotel. Sometimes it's easier just to jump in a taxi (always available at the front of the hotel) - they may be a bit more expensive but are much quicker and more convenient.I really would have liked a tea/coffee making facility and mini bar in my room but for the price I paid, I'm not complaining!	
Jan 28 2009 	Noisy Stratosphere	This was our first trip to Vegas, as part of a three week road trip around the West Coast. The Stratosphere was the first hotel we came across, so we just walked in, and tried our luck at getting a decent room. We were in luck and we got a suite for three nights for $95 dollars a night. The hotel was a fair distance from the strip, but you could get a bus called the &quot;Deuce&quot; easily which would take you down the strip for around $3. The room was nice, with a Jacuzzi,and a big bed. The first night was great, quiet and we both had a decent night's sleep, but on the second night, the noise coming from the Air Con units on the roof was awful, and then if that wasn;t bad enough, the noise then coming from the water system's within the hotel ensured that we didn't get any sleep for the second and third night. We tried changing room's, but to avail, as they wanted us to move all our things out of the room at 3am in the morning!!! We did get a bit of money knocked of the bill. but not a massive amount, around $50. The staff at the hotel were all pretty rude and unhelpful.	
